.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkerala%2Fhuman-wildlife-conflicts-inter-state-panel-with-kerala-karnataka-and-tamil-nadu-officials-formed%2Farticle67837532.ece%5C%22%3E%20committee%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20to%20release%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2024%2F02%2F11%2Fmission-belur-makhana-forest-department-of-kerala-slams-karnataka-for-delaying-crucial-assistance.html%5C%22%3Eopposition%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20other%20states%20against%20Karnataka%20releasing%20its%20%E2%80%9Cproblem%E2%80%9D%20elephants%20at%20the%20border%20areas.%20In%20this%20ongoing%20narrative%2C%20now%20highly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkerala%2F2024%2FFeb%2F19%2Fkerala-human-wildlife-conflict-turns-political%5C%22%3Epolitical%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20some%20political%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20union%20minister%2C%20Bhupender%20Yadav%20%E2%80%93%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkarnataka%2F2024%2FFeb%2F22%2Fkerala-shouldve-compensated-victim-union-minister-bhupender-yadav%5C%22%3Evoiced%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20Karnataka%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20pay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fkarnataka-awards-compensation-to-man-trampled-by-its-elephant-in-rahul-gandhis-wayanad%2Farticleshow%2F107826452.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E15%20lakhs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20compensation%20to%20the%20deceased%E2%80%99s%20family%20in%20Wayanad.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20note%20here%20that%20this%20was%20not%20a%20regular%20elephant%20but%20a%20radio-collared%2C%20translocated%20one.%20Also%2C%20the%20Kerala%20forest%20department%20points%20towards%20the%20Karnataka%20forest%20department%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.mathrubhumi.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2Fwayanad-jumbo-attack-sparks-off-blame-game-1.9312683%5C%22%3Edelay%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20relaying%20information%20on%20the%20elephant%20movements%20%E2%80%93%20data%20that%20could%20have%20helped%20avoid%20human%20death.%20Unfortunately%2C%20one%20of%20the%20key%20causes%20of%20this%20escalating%20issue%2C%20the%20adoption%20and%20impact%20of%20the%20translocation%20of%20elephants%20as%20a%20mitigation%20measure%2C%20is%20still%20not%20being%20addressed.%20Many%20scientists%20state%20translocation%20is%20a%20political%20phenomenon%20rather%20than%20an%20ecological%20one.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20several%20species%2C%20translocation%20is%20counter-productive%2C%20either%20for%20people%20or%20for%20the%20species%2C%E2%80%9D%20confirms%20Sayan%20Banerjee%2C%20a%20doctoral%20scholar%20looking%20at%20human-elephant%20interactions%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20highly-cited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3517608%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTranslocation%2520caused%2520wider%2520propagation%2520and%2Cmitigation%2520and%2520elephant%2520conservation%2520goals.%5C%22%3Estudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20viability%20of%20translocating%20Asian%20elephants%20as%20a%20mitigation%20measure%20proves%20how%20it%20%E2%80%9Ctranslocates%E2%80%9D%20the%20problem%20elsewhere.%20In%20Karnataka%2C%20one%20of%20the%20very%20few%20states%20in%20India%20using%20this%20method%20extensively%2C%20that%20is%20literally%20what%20is%20unfolding%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20459px)%2085vw%2C%20459px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22459%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553.jpg%20968w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553-242x300.jpg%20242w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553-826x1024.jpg%20826w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701002%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22569%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20elephant%20named%20%E2%80%9CThaneer%20Komban%E2%80%9D%20which%20died%20after%20being%20re-captured%20from%20the%20wild%20in%20Wayanad%20district%2C%20Kerala.%20Photo%3A%20Vinod%20Krishnan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Thanneer%20%E2%80%93%20an%20elephant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkochi%2Ftragic-death-of-thanneer-komban-after-circuslike-crowd%2Farticleshow%2F107395430.cms%5C%22%3Etranslocated%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Hassan%20to%20Bandipur%20Tiger%20Reserve%20in%20January%20this%20year%20after%20locals%20(as%20per%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fthesundaystandard%2F2024%2FFeb%2F04%2Fwild-elephant-captured-by-forest-dept-from-karnatakas-hassan-district-dies-of-heart-attack-when-released%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E)%20raised%20concerns%20of%20the%20animal%E2%80%99s%20crop-raiding%20behavior%20%E2%80%93%20ventured%20into%20neighboring%20Wayanad%20district%20in%20Kerala%20within%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20his%20release.%20After%20protests%20by%20locals%2C%20the%20Kerala%20forest%20department%20decided%20to%20recapture%20the%20elephant.%20The%20operation%20lasted%20for%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkerala%2F2024%2FFeb%2F04%2Fthanneerkomban-dies-experts-point-to-lapses-in-mission%5C%22%3E17%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Thanneer%20died%20in%20an%20elephant%20camp%20in%20Bandipur%2C%20where%20he%20was%20brought%20after%20the%20capture.%20Some%20claim%20the%20death%20resulted%20from%20shock%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkochi%2Ftragic-death-of-thanneer-komban-after-circuslike-crowd%2Farticleshow%2F107395430.cms%5C%22%3Etrauma%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20others%20speak%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.mathrubhumi.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2Fseveral-pellet-mark-wounds-found-on-thaneer-komban-s-body-1.9295919%5C%22%3Einjuries%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20week%2C%20yet%20another%20radio-collared%20translocated%20elephant%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Belur%20Makhna%20%E2%80%93%20relocated%20from%20Hassan%20to%20Bandipur%2C%20also%20moved%20into%20Kerala.%20In%20the%20interactions%20that%20followed%2C%20a%20man%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2024%2F02%2F10%2Fwild-elephant-mananthavady-section-144.html%5C%22%3Edied%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20over%20ten%20days%2C%20close%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2024%2F02%2F14%2Fbelur-makhna-rrt-forest-darting-another-elephant-third-day.html%5C%22%3E200%3C%2Fa%3E%20staff%20of%20the%20Kerala%20forest%20department%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkerala%2F2024%2FFeb%2F16%2Fkerala-proposal-to-control-wildlife-population-draws-flak%5C%22%3E%20an%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkerala%2F2024%2FFeb%2F16%2Fkerala-proposal-to-control-wildlife-population-draws-flak%5C%22%3E18-22-member%3C%2Fa%3E%20team%20from%20Karnataka%20were%20looking%20for%20the%20Belur%20Makhna%20to%20recapture%20him.%20The%20Kerala%20forest%20department%20also%20roped%20in%20sharpshooter%20Nawab%20Shafath%20Ali%20Khan%20for%20the%20operation.%20As%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fbelur-makhna-back-in-ktaka-as-kerala-tries-to-capture-it%2Farticleshow%2F107956927.cms%5C%22%3EFebruary%2024%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Belur%20Makhna%20is%20said%20to%20have%20reentered%20Karnataka.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20wait-and-watch%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20negative%20impacts%20of%20translocating%20elephants%20have%20transpired%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cborder%20issue%E2%80%9D.%20Arikomban%20from%20Kerala%2C%20for%20example%2C%20in%20a%20day-long%20effort%2C%20was%20captured%20by%20over%20150%20forest%20staff%20and%20four%20%3Cem%3Ekumkis%3C%2Fem%3E%20(captive%20elephants%20that%20are%20trained%20to%20capture%20wild%20ones).%20The%20department%20moved%20him%20to%20Periyar%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Frogue-elephant-arikomban-captured-tamil-nadu-8647063%2F%5C%22%3Erecaptured%3C%2Fa%3E%20again%20after%20he%20moved%20into%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Similarly%2C%20elephant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2023%2F01%2F09%2Fwild-elephant-pm2-tranquilised-forest-department.html%5C%22%3EPM2%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20post-translocation%2C%20was%20recaptured%20after%20it%20was%20found%20in%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudies%20globally%20have%20shown%20how%20a%20scientifically%20carried%20out%20translocation%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20unobtrusive%20to%20a%20large%20extent%20%E2%80%93%20still%20leads%20to%20elevated%20physiological%20stress%20response%20for%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.co.za%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.10520%2FEJC117293%5C%22%3E30%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20release%20of%20the%20animal.%20T%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0003347206003460%5C%22%3Eranslocation%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20also%20generate%20various%20stressors%20at%20any%20stage%20of%20their%20execution%2C%20which%20have%20additive%20or%20cumulative%20effects%20on%20animals.%20So%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20surprising%20that%20these%20translocated%20animals%20are%20already%20stressed.%20Also%2C%20as%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8800974%2F%5C%22%3Estudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20proved%20over%20the%20years%2C%20most%20translocated%20elephants%20move%20widely%20to%20return%20to%20their%20home%20range%20or%20try%20to%20establish%20home%20ranges%20in%20new%20areas.%20Interactions%20have%20always%20cropped%20up%20in%20these%20areas%2C%20as%20seen%20in%20the%20above-mentioned%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20translocation%20worth%20the%20effort%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20most%20of%20these%20translocation%20efforts%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Fwild-elephant-karuppan-captured-in-talavadi-hill-translocated-to-thattakarai-forest-range-in-erode-division%2Farticle66747198.ece%5C%22%3E%20authorities%20declare%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Fwild-elephant-karuppan-captured-in-talavadi-hill-translocated-to-thattakarai-forest-range-in-erode-division%2Farticle66747198.ece%5C%22%3Ecurfews%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20close%20down%20schools%20and%20colleges%20for%20a%20day%20or%20two.%20For%20many%20local%20communities%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fvillagers-intensify-protest-against-relocation-of-rogue-elephant-arikomban-from-idukki-to-parambikulam-wildlife-sanctuary-in-kerala-101681126167444.html%5C%22%3Eareas%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20capture%20and%20release%2C%20the%20stress%20is%20unbounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20one%20of%20the%20elephants%20from%20Hassan%20was%20radio-collared%20and%20translocated%20to%20Bandipur%2C%20a%20scientist%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20operation%2C%20on%20anonymity%2C%20explained%3A%20%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20these%20translocated%20elephants%20make%20attempts%20to%20go%20back%20to%20their%20home%20range.%20We%20have%20also%20found%20interactions%20in%20areas%20of%20release.%20Locals%20now%20believe%20most%20of%20the%20radio-collared%20elephants%20to%20be%20those%20translocated%20from%20other%20areas.%20Hence%2C%20they%20protest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20IUCN%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fportals.iucn.org%2Flibrary%2Fsites%2Flibrary%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2003-089.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20guidelines%20for%20the%20translocation%20of%20African%20elephants%20states%20that%20communities%20around%20the%20release%20site%20should%20be%20consulted%20and%20kept%20informed%20for%20the%20long-term%20security%20of%20the%20translocated%20elephant.%20None%20of%20the%20forest%20departments%20in%20South%20India%20seek%20permission%20from%20locals%20in%20the%20release%20area%20before%20translocation.%20In%20Tamil%20Nadu%20last%20year%2C%20an%20elephant%20called%20Makhna%20was%20translocated%20for%20the%20second%20time%20and%20spent%20an%20agonising%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Ftamil-nadu%2F2023%2FFeb%2F25%2Fmakhna-finally-findshome-after-200-km-ride-24-hours-on-truck-2550714.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCOIMBATORE%253A%2520The%252045%252Dyear%252D%2Cits%2520release%2520in%2520their%2520localities.%5C%22%3E24%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20truck%20traveling%20200%20km%3A%20because%20locals%20in%20two%20separate%20areas%20protested%20against%20Makhna%E2%80%99s%20release%20near%20their%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20almost%20all%20cases%20of%20translocation%20of%20elephants%20in%20these%20states%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20operation%20runs%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCaptures%20are%20expensive.%20The%20amount%20for%20tranquillisation%20and%20the%20transport%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekumkis%3C%2Fem%3E%20alone%20costs%20lakhs%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20forest%20official%20from%20Kodagu%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Karnataka%20spends%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmysuru%2Fktaka-spends-rs-22-lakh-to-radio-collar-each-wild-jumbo%2Farticleshow%2F105830251.cms%5C%22%3ERs%2022%20lakh%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20radio-collar%20an%20elephant.%20According%20to%20some%20news%20reports%2C%20Kerala%20spent%20Rs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2023%2F08%2F05%2Fmission-arikomban-pt7-kerala-spend-rs33-lakh.html%5C%22%3E15.85%20lakh%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20translocate%20Arikomban%20and%20Rs%2017.32%20lakh%20in%20capturing%20and%20relocating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkerala-forest-department-captures-rogue-elephant-pt-7-in-palakkad-renames-as-dhoni-1183697.html%5C%22%3EPT7%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20an%20elephant%20camp.%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20when%20rehoming%20some%20of%20the%20captured%20elephants%2C%20at%20times%2C%20spends%20Rs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Fwork-to-construct-kraal-begins-at-chadivayal-elephant-camp%2Farticle25216940.ece%5C%22%3E10%20lakh%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20single%20%3Cem%3Ekraal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(an%20enclosure%20made%20to%20constrict%20and%20tame%20a%20wild%20elephant%20into%20submission).%20Authorities%20often%20spend%20more%20than%20Rs%202-3%20lakh%20on%20cage%20construction%20to%20transport%20the%20animal.%20Then%20comes%20the%20cost%20of%20transporting%20%3Cem%3Ekumkis%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20sometimes%2C%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkarnataka%2Foperation-jumbo-to-capture-wild-elephants-resumes-in-karnataka-2844812%5C%22%3Eeight%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20used%2C%20like%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fbengaluru-news%2Fkarnataka-forest-department-resumes-operation-jumbo-to-capture-wild-elephants-101704992262384.html%5C%22%3EKarnataka%E2%80%99s%20Operation%20Jumbo%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20aims%20to%20capture%20elephants%20and%20fix%20radio%20collars%20in%20Hassan%20district.%20Costs%20covering%20transport%2C%20earthmovers%20(numbers%20exceeding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Foperation-black-to-capture-wild-elephant-begins-at-talavadi-hills-in-erode%2Farticle66369889.ece%5C%22%3E100%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20above%20at%20times)%2C%20staff%2C%20their%20food%20and%20stay%20for%20all%20the%20days%20spent%20searching%20and%20capturing%20an%20elephant%20%E2%80%93%20are%20additional.%20The%20cost%20of%20the%20upkeep%20of%20elephants%20captured%20for%20captivity%20is%20over%2011%20lakhs%20for%20one%20individual%20for%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2023%2F03%2F26%2Fkerala-government-spends-crores-wild-elephants.html%5C%22%3ERTI%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20all%20these%20go%20into%20a%20single%20capture%20and%20translocation%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20science%20behind%20identification%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20discussing%20plans%20for%20Operation%20Jumbo%2C%20a%20senior%20forest%20department%20official%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fbengaluru-news%2Fkarnataka-forest-department-resumes-operation-jumbo-to-capture-wild-elephants-101704992262384.html%5C%22%3Epress%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20would%20start%20our%20operations%20in%20Belur%20taluk%20where%20more%20than%2050%20wild%20elephants%20had%20come.%20These%20wild%20jumbos%2C%20which%20came%20around%20two%20months%20ago%20into%20the%20Taluk%20area%2C%20have%20to%20be%20driven%20away%20to%20the%20elephant%20habitat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20knee-jerk%20reaction%20to%20interactions%20and%20an%20unscientific%20method%20of%20identifying%20elephants%20for%20translocation%20has%20disrupted%20the%20lives%20of%20several%20elephants%20not%20responsible%20for%20interactions.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20has%20not%20addressed%20conflicts%20with%20humans%20on%20the%20ground.%20Locals%20have%20also%20expressed%20anger%20at%20such%20mishaps%20in%20the%20past.%20As%20in%20the%20case%20of%20elephant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fa-case-of-mistaken-identity-locals-claim-karnataka-forest-dept-captured-wrong-elephant-as-rampage-continues-6773881.html%5C%22%3EBhaira%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20Chikkamagaluru%2C%20whose%20capture%20led%20to%20further%20protests%20by%20locals%20claiming%20the%20forest%20department%20picked%20the%20wrong%20elephant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20people%20have%20mourned%20such%20unscientific%20decisions%2C%20like%20in%20the%20recent%20case%20with%20elephant%20Thanneer%2C%20where%20several%20expressed%20their%20grievances%20on%20social%20media.%20Vinod%20Krishnan%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20in%20Hassan%20for%20a%20decade%20handling%20human-elephant%20interactions%20and%20has%20observed%20Thaneer%20since%202018%2C%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThaneer%20would%20simply%20walk%20away%20at%20the%20sight%20of%20any%20human%20being%20around.%20He%20kept%20to%20himself%20and%20did%20not%20harm%20anyone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20public%20post%2C%20Krishnan%20recounted%20Thaneer%E2%80%99s%20story%20as%20an%20individual%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20behavior%20and%20life%3A%20who%2C%20in%20public%20memory%2C%20had%20passed%20on%2C%20being%20remembered%20as%20just%20another%20featureless%20%E2%80%9Crogue%E2%80%9D%20elephant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fcontent%2F647543%2Fneed-restore-elephant-corridors.html%5C%22%3E2017%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20interacted%20with%20locals%20near%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20Cauvery%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary%20after%20elephants%20raided%20over%2055%20farms%20in%20a%20single%20day.%20They%20demanded%20barricades%2C%20the%20timely%20presence%20of%20the%20forest%20department%20during%20the%20crisis%2C%20and%20compensation.%20No%20one%20spoke%20of%20capture.%20However%2C%20that%20has%20changed%20now.%20The%20use%20of%20translocation%20as%20mitigation%20has%20doubled%20since%202014%20after%20authorities%20captured%2F%20translocated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fwith-human-elephant-conflict-taking-more-lives-on-both-sides-stakeholders-are-split-over-a-sustainable-solution%2Farticleshow%2F68337524.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E22%3C%2Fa%3E%20wild%20elephants%20from%20Hassan%20based%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.peepli.org%2Fstories%2Fthe-elephants-must-go%2F%5C%22%3Erecommendations%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20scientists%20and%20members%20of%20the%20then%20Karnataka%20Elephant%20Task%20Force.%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20also%20triggered%20dependence%20and%20a%20pattern%20in%20locals%2C%20who%20have%20since%20been%20requesting%20capture%20as%20the%20only%20solution%20to%20interactions%20across%20Karnataka%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froundglasssustain.com%2Fconservation%2Felephant-translocation%5C%22%3E%20evidenced%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20mitigation%20measure%2C%20often%20leading%20to%20more%20interactions%2C%20this%20solution%20has%20been%20used%20in%20reckless%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fbangalore%2F74-elephants-captured-rehabilitated-in-sakleshpura-and-belur-taluks-of-karnataka-8080952%2F%5C%22%3E%20frequency%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20which%20is%20expensive%2C%20highly%20stress-inducing%20and%20risky%20to%20humans%20and%20elephants%20but%20has%20yielded%20(mostly)%20a%20cycle%20of%20misfortunes%3A%20conflict-%20capture%20%E2%80%93%20translocation-conflict%20%E2%80%93%20conflict-recapture.%20Repeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20resorting%20to%20intrusive%20solutions%20like%20translocation%20is%20rarely%20adopted%20by%20states%20that%20witness%20more%20interactions%20than%20Karnataka%2C%20such%20as%20Assam%20and%20West%20Bengal.%20Banerjee%20says%20that%20investing%20in%20short%20term%2C%20band-aid%2C%20tech-only%20solutions%20(such%20as%20radio%20collaring%20and%20translocations)%20for%20long-persisting%20issues%20like%20human-wildlife%20interactions%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20always%20help.%20Addressing%20the%20local%20driving%20factors%20%E2%80%93%20political%2C%20social%2C%20and%20cultural%20%E2%80%93%20is%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20needs%20to%20go%20a%20bit%20deeper%20to%20understand%20the%20roots%20through%20which%20these%20narratives%20were%20set%20and%20put%20into%20motion.%20We%20are%20solution-centric%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20new%20techs%20to%20solve%20an%20apparent%20unsolvable%20problem.%20The%20assumption%20of%20wildlife%20conflict%20management%20is%20that%20we%20cannot%20treat%20socio-political%20causes%20and%20find%20newer%20solutions%20(or%20tech)%20to%20pacify%20the%20situation.%20Both%20elephants%20and%20people%20who%20live%20around%20these%20elephants%20are%20the%20losers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eletellnow.wordpress.com%5C%22%3EGana%20Kedlaya%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20environment%20reporter%20based%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710067500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160754%2F1000016556.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthree-states-to-work-together-to-address-the-elephant-in-the-room%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20ongoing%20human-elephant%20interaction%20crisis%20in%20South%20India%2C%20the%20role%20of%20translocation%20and%20its%20impact%20needs%20attention.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthree-states-to-work-together-to-address-the-elephant-in-the-room%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22And%20Then%20There%20Will%20Be%20None%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16094246%2Fimage1440x560cropped.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20child%20victim%E2%80%99s%20body%20is%20the%20moral%20Ground%20Zero%20of%20conflict%20and%20the%20global%20silence%20around%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FAfghan_Girl%23%2Fmedia%2FFile%3ASharbat_Gula.jpg%5C%22%3EAfghan%20Girl%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2015)%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficonicphotos.files.wordpress.com%2F2009%2F08%2Fkevin-carter-vulture.jpg%5C%22%3Evulture%20and%20the%20little%20girl%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2013)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.arabnews.com%2Fnode%2F978831%2F%257B%257B%5C%22%3EAylan%20Kurdi%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2015)%20and%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F09%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fyazan-kafarneh-gaza-starvation.html%3Funlocked_article_code%3D1.bU0.L7Pa.YczkkiFGRDW2%26smid%3Durl-share%5C%22%3EYazan%20Kafarneh%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2024).%20Media%20photographs%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20armed%20conflict%20on%20children%2C%20arguably%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20in%20any%20condition%20of%20conflict%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmeaning-is-a-physiognomy-or-the-child-victim-as-the-face-of-the-modern-age%5C%22%3Eideal%20victim%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20have%20marched%20endlessly%20through%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20famous%20social%20documentary%20filmmaker%20Jacob%20Riis%20captured%20New%20York%E2%80%99s%20poorer%20neighbourhoods%20in%20his%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Children%20of%20the%20Poor%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1892)%20as%20a%20mode%20of%20raising%20awareness%20of%20the%20social%20state%20of%20the%20expanding%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fexhibits%2Fexhibit%2Fchildren-beyond-armed-conflict%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20employed%20such%20photographs%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20own%20ends.%20UNICEF%20began%20by%20capturing%20child%20victims%20of%20poverty%20in%20the%20late%2019th%20century%2C%20and%20employed%20the%20pictures%20to%20solicit%20sympathy%20and%20contributions%20but%20also%20ramp%20up%20a%20humanitarian%20morality%20around%20the%20figure%20of%20the%20child%20and%20uneven%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F27895958%5C%22%3EPaula%20S.%20Fass%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20noted%20in%20her%20essay%2C%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Rights%20Convention%20adopted%20in%201959%20made%20use%20of%20such%20pictures%20to%20underline%20its%20point.%20Collections%20such%20as%20UNICEF%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.unhcr.org%2Fen%2Fdocuments%2Fdetails%2F40082%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EUnder%20Siege%3A%20The%20Devastating%20Impacts%20on%20Children%20of%20Three%20Years%20of%20Conflict%20in%20Syria%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2015)%20were%20put%20out%20for%20later%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20longer%20recognisable%20as%20persons%2C%20given%20their%20ruined%20state%2C%20the%20children%20look%20out%20from%20the%20UNICEF%20photographs%2C%20or%20do%20not%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EYazan%20Al-Kafarneh%2C%2013%2C%20died%20of%20malnutrition%20today.%20He%20was%20killed%20by%20Israel%20through%20starvation.%20Many%20more%20children%20are%20dead%20or%20dying.%20What%20more%20horrors%20need%20to%20occur%20before%20putting%20an%20end%20to%20this%20genocide%3F!!%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FkhpCGDAQe2%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FkhpCGDAQe2%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Ambassador%20Majed%20Bamya%20%F0%9F%87%B5%F0%9F%87%B8%20(%40majedbamya)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmajedbamya%2Fstatus%2F1764646518265430118%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%204%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20extreme%20vulnerability%20of%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh%2C%20beyond%20their%20fragile%20bodies%2C%20the%20photographs%20achieve%20something%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20children%20traditionally%20associated%20with%20not%20just%20innocence%20but%20embodying%20potential%20are%20captured%20embedded%20in%20a%20context%20in%20which%20no%20future%20can%20possibly%20unfold.%20Starvation%2C%20absence%20of%20healthcare%20and%20unrelenting%20conflict%20are%20the%20contexts%20in%20which%20a%20Kafarneh-with-potential%20becomes%20a%20victim%2C%20one%20whose%20potential%20has%20been%20erased%20fully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhich%20means%20to%20say%2C%20the%20sites%2C%20whether%20bombed%20ruins%20or%20hospital%20beds%2C%20are%20sites%20where%20no%20future%20abides.%20If%20potential%20and%20capability%20require%20a%20sustaining%20environment%20in%20which%20to%20reach%20fruition%2C%20then%20the%20context%20in%20which%20Kurdi%20or%20Kafarneh%20are%20embedded%20ensures%20that%20no%20potential%20is%20ever%20likely%20to%20be%20fulfilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20photographs%20then%20are%20not%20of%20the%20children%20alone%3A%20they%20point%20to%20the%20material%20conditions%20in%20which%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20future%20alone%20rests.%20The%20pictures%20are%20not%20about%20the%20present%3A%20they%20are%20about%20a%20%3Cem%3Efuture%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20which%2C%20possibly%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20children%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20the%20scenes%20of%20destruction%20that%20we%20see%20unfolding%20on%20our%20screens%20today%2C%20whether%20of%20barren%20lands%20or%20devastated%20lands%2C%20force%20us%20to%20shift%20from%20ruin%20to%20rubble.%20The%20ruin%2C%20which%20has%20its%20own%20melancholic%20appeal%20and%20sense%20of%20mystery%2C%20is%20now%20just%20plain%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20child%20victim%20does%20not%20connect%20to%20the%20ruin%3A%20s%2Fhe%20is%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20rubble%2C%20a%20part%20of%20it%2C%20broken%2C%20dismembered%20and%20poignantly%20separated%20from%20a%20context%20in%20which%20s%2Fhe%20would%20have%20otherwise%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20landscape%20of%20conflict%20where%20Kafarneh%20is%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98found%E2%80%99%20(a%20wholly%20inappropriate%20word%2C%20given%20that%20he%20starved%20to%20death%20in%20his%20%E2%80%98home%E2%80%99)%20is%20a%20place%20where%20matter%20has%20lost%20its%20form.%20The%20hospital%2C%20the%20home%20and%20the%20school%20are%20no%20longer%20the%20same%3A%20their%20form%20has%20been%20broken%20down%20into%20bricks%2C%20mortar%20and%20steel%20due%20to%20the%20bombings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F4D0Xc6ppHro%3Fsi%3DSpUupQaVY5JUWrjj%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaterial%20matter%2C%20which%20had%20been%20formed%20into%20structures%20for%20a%20Kafarneh%20to%20live%20in%2C%20play%20in%20and%20study%20in%2C%20has%20returned%20to%20a%20pre-form%2C%20by%20which%20I%20mean%20a%20state%20%3Cem%3Eprior%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20all%20form%20state%3A%20rubble.%20The%20ruins%20of%20buildings%20may%20still%20be%20functional%2C%20at%20least%20minimally.%20But%20their%20intended%20service%20and%20purpose%20are%20altered%20once%20the%20ruination%20has%20set%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20loss%20of%20form%20and%20function%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20hospital%2C%20the%20home%2C%20the%20school%20%E2%80%93%20that%20produces%20the%20child%20victim.%20Kafarneh%20died%20in%20a%20hospital%20bed%2C%20but%20he%20arrives%20via%20a%20landscape%20smashed%20to%20smithereens%20and%20in%20a%20state%20of%20advanced%20starvation%2C%20according%20to%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hospital%20is%20of%20no%20functional%20use%20because%20life%20among%20the%20rubble%20has%20made%20it%20impossible%20that%20the%20new%20matter%20(the%20form%20and%20function%20of%20the%20hospital)%20can%20revive%20that%20life.%20Just%20as%20the%20hospital%2C%20home%20and%20school%20are%20rendered%20into%20waste%2C%20so%20is%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20body%20that%20occupies%20those%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20a%20tragic%20correlation%20between%20the%20wasting%20%E2%80%93%20intended%2C%20of%20course%2C%20through%20bombings%20%E2%80%93%20building%20and%20the%20wasted%20child.%20In%20these%20spaces%2C%20the%20human%20form%2C%20particularly%20of%20the%20child%2C%20is%20inverted%20into%20mere%20flesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruined%20body%20of%20Kafarneh%2C%20within%20the%20precincts%20of%20the%20hospital%20where%20he%20died%2C%20does%20not%20point%20to%20the%20hospital.%20It%20points%20to%20the%20landscape%20he%20came%20%3Cem%3Ethrough%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20ruined%20or%20damaged%20hospital%20is%20newness%20because%20the%20original%20hospital%20is%20only%20in%20the%20past.%20Likewise%20is%20Kafarneh%20lying%20in%20bed%2C%20emaciated%20to%20a%20point%20where%20there%20is%20little%20matter%20(flesh)%20on%20him%20(and%20the%20eyes%20seem%20overly%20large%20as%20a%20result).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20and%20the%20bombing%20therefore%20produce%20new%20matter%3A%20the%20ruined%20hospital%20of%20the%20present%20and%20the%20starving%20body%20in%20the%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20the%20dissolving%20human%20body%20%E2%80%93%20the%20liquefaction%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20stuff%20of%20nightmares%20and%20much%20Gothic%20and%20neo-Gothic%20horror.%20But%20neither%20Kurdi%20nor%20Kafarneh%20are%20dissolved%20bodies.%20The%20horror%20we%20see%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Ecorpus%20intacta%3C%2Fem%3E%20but%20diminished.%20It%20invokes%20greater%20horror%2C%20one%20could%20argue%2C%20not%20because%20it%20is%20broken%20but%20because%20it%20is%20whole%20and%20yet%20not-alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-worlds-indifference-to-palestinian-genocide-will-cost-more-lives%5C%22%3EThe%20World%E2%80%99s%20Indifference%20to%20Palestinian%20Genocide%20Will%20Cost%20More%20Lives%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriting%20about%20the%20Abu%20Ghraib%20visuals%2C%20the%20critic%20Susan%20Sontag%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20live%20is%20to%20be%20photographed%2C%20to%20have%20a%20record%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20and%20therefore%20to%20go%20on%20with%20one%E2%80%99s%20life%20oblivious%2C%20or%20claiming%20to%20be%20oblivious%2C%20to%20the%20camera%E2%80%99s%20nonstop%20attentions.%20But%20to%20live%20is%20also%20to%20pose.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20sense%2C%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh%20are%20posed%3A%20captured%20on%20camera%20in%20a%20particular%20state.%20Except%20that%20this%20state%20is%20not%20a%20pose%20emanating%20from%20life.%20It%20is%20a%20record%2C%20to%20adapt%20Sontag%E2%80%99s%20words%2C%20of%20how%20a%20life%20%3Cem%3Ecould%20not%20be%20lived%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eany%20more%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20photograph%20captures%20a%20body%20transitioned%20from%20the%20living%20to%20the%20non-living%3A%20just%20inert%20matter%20on%20a%20beach%20(Kurdi)%20or%20a%20bed%20(Kafarneh).%20The%20human%20descends%2C%20reversing%20the%20normative%20of%20life%20lived%20towards%20a%20future%2C%20into%20the%20abhuman%20(starvation%2C%20in%20this%20most%20recent%20case)%20and%20eventually%20the%20non-living.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%209%2F11%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EFalling%20Man%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Don%20DeLillo%20writes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20something%20that%20belonged%20to%20another%20landscape%2C%20something%20inserted%2C%20a%20conjuring%20that%20resembled%20for%20the%20briefest%20second%20some%20half-seen%20image%20only%20half%20believed%20in%20the%20seeing%2C%20when%20the%20witness%20wonders%20what%20has%20happened%20to%20the%20meaning%20of%20things%2C%20to%20tree%2C%20stone%2C%20wind%2C%20simple%20words%20lost%20in%20the%20falling%20ash.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20it%20is%20another%20landscape%3A%20a%20once-pulsing%2C%20thriving%20land%20is%20transformed%20into%20unrecognisable%20forms%20of%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20essay%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbooks%2F2001%2Fdec%2F22%2Ffiction.dondelillo%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20Ruins%20of%20the%20Future%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20this%20same%20Don%20DeLillo%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CFor%20all%20those%20who%20may%20want%20what%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%2C%20there%20are%20all%20those%20who%20do%20not.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20did%20want%20the%20same%20thing%20for%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh%3A%20life.%20So%20we%20%3Cem%3Eknow%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20meaning%20of%20things%20buried%20beneath%20the%20ash%20of%20this%20smoking%20rubble%3A%20a%20future%20ended%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there%20will%20be%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fpramod-k-nayar%5C%22%3EPramod%20K.%20Nayar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710066801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16094246%2Fimage1440x560cropped.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fand-then-there-were-none-yazan-kafarneh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Traditionally%2C%20the%20dissolving%20human%20body%20is%20the%20stuff%20of%20nightmares.%20But%20Yazan%20Kafarneh%20is%20not%20a%20dissolved%20body.%20The%20horror%20we%20see%20is%20the%20corpus%20intacta%20but%20diminished.%20It%20invokes%20greater%20horror%20not%20because%20it%20is%20broken%20but%20because%20it%20is%20whole%20and%20yet%20not-alive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fand-then-there-were-none-yazan-kafarneh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ChatGPT%20uses%2017k%20times%20more%20electricity%20than%20US%20household%20in%20a%20day%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710066266000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108368117%2Cimgsize-1769792.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Falarming-ai-numbers-chatgpt-uses-17000-times-more-electricity-than-an-average-us-household-in-a-day%2Farticleshow%2F108368128.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0