are%20built%2C%20buildings%20raised%2C%20clothes%20worn%2C%20toys%20and%20gadgets%20and%20appliances%20used.%20More%20people%20are%20traveling%20farther%20and%20more%20often.%20And%20the%20global%20Gross%20Domestic%20Product%E2%80%94possibly%20the%20most%20revered%20metric%20in%20all%20of%20human%20history%E2%80%94has%20been%20going%20up%20and%20up%20and%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGraphs%20of%20consumption%20or%20production%20of%20various%20commodities%20and%20goods%E2%80%94like%20sand%20or%20cement%2C%20steel%20or%20cars%2C%20houses%20or%20furniture%2C%20and%20a%20host%20of%20other%20things%E2%80%94as%20well%20as%20the%20size%20of%20the%20human%20population%2C%20emissions%20of%20industrial%20waste%2C%20or%20other%20metrics%20reflecting%20our%20use%20of%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20nearly%20all%20indicate%20a%20strikingly%20similar%20growth%20pattern%20across%20time%3A%20around%20the%201950s%2C%20all%20these%20things%20began%20to%20accelerate.%20Geologists%2C%20anthropologists%2C%20and%20others%20call%20this%20astonishing%20trend%20the%20%3Cem%3EGreat%20Acceleration%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%20began%20two%20hundred%20years%20prior%20to%20this.%20So%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%2020th%20Century%20to%20fuel%20such%20a%20rush%20in%20the%20consumption%20of%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20the%20associated%20pollution%20of%20air%2C%20water%2C%20and%20soil%2C%20and%20a%20dramatic%20acceleration%20in%20the%20extinction%20of%20species%20and%20loss%20of%20biodiversity%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112214%2F1280px-Anthropocene-GreatAccelerationSocioEconomicTrends-1750-2010.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112214%2F1280px-Anthropocene-GreatAccelerationSocioEconomicTrends-1750-2010.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112214%2F1280px-Anthropocene-GreatAccelerationSocioEconomicTrends-1750-2010-300x191.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112214%2F1280px-Anthropocene-GreatAccelerationSocioEconomicTrends-1750-2010-1024x650.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700957%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22762%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESocioeconomic%20Trends%20of%20the%20Great%20Acceleration%2C%20showing%20the%20rise%20in%20consumption%20from%201750%20to%202010.%20The%20data%20graphically%20displayed%20is%20scaled%20for%20each%20datum%E2%80%99s%202010%20value.%20Source%20data%20is%20from%20the%20International%20Geosphere-Biosphere%20Programme.%20Chart%3A%20Bryanmackinnon%2FCC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20is%20petroleum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPetroleum%2C%20or%20oil%2C%20is%20the%20most%20energy-dense%20combustible%20we%20know%20of.%20It%20remains%20a%20liquid%20at%20ordinary%20temperatures%20and%20pressures%3A%20easily%20pumped%2C%20piped%2C%20tanked%2C%20stored%2C%20carried%20to%20wherever%20it%E2%80%99s%20needed%20to%20be%20burned%20on-site%E2%80%94or%20even%20within%20the%20bowels%20of%20a%20small%2C%20moving%20vehicle%E2%80%94none%20of%20which%20coal%20nor%20any%20other%20fuel%20can%20do%20so%20easily%20or%20cheaply.%20The%20Great%20Acceleration%20was%20driven%20by%20the%20advancing%20availability%20of%20petroleum%20to%20power%20internal%20combustion%20engines%2C%20making%20it%20possible%20to%20interlink%20the%20world%20through%20industrial%20shipping%20and%20trucking.%20This%20drew%20more%20of%20the%20world%20into%20the%20booming%20capitalist%20economy%20centred%20in%20the%20West%2C%20especially%20the%20United%20States%2C%20to%20a%20degree%20that%20simply%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20been%20possible%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20century%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fgovernance%2Frich-land-poor-people-what-will-be-the-future-of-generations-growing-up-in-jharkhand-s-coal-belt-89534%5C%22%3Ecoal%20companies%20have%20taken%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DC33Wfhu3BX0%5C%22%3Escorched%20the%20ground%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Jharia%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20turning%20what%20had%20been%20a%20home%20to%20Adivasi%20communities%20into%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DUzivaxYf1iM%5C%22%3Euninhabitable%20hellscape%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20of%20those%20who%20thereby%20lost%20their%20lands%20and%20livelihoods%20became%20coal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2019%2F10%2Fthe-burning-coalfields-of-jharia-belch-poison-for-local-residents%2F%5C%22%3Eminers%2C%20who%20today%20remain%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F05%2Ffear-of-job-loss-and-social-security-run-high-among-jharkhand-mine-workers%2F%5C%22%3Epool%20of%20unsupported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1043473%2Ftheyve-nothing-else-here-the-poor-steal-coal-in-jharkhands-mining-hubs-in-order-to-survive%5C%22%3Eimpoverished%20labourers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20daily%20exposed%20to%20toxic%20levels%20of%20pollution%E2%80%94even%20as%20they%20remain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiforest.global%2F2020%2F11%2Fjharkhand-contributes-to-32-of-the-countrys-reserves-but-loses-more-than-it-gains-from-coal%2F%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20most%20underserved%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20electrification%20they%20bring%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%94a%20prime%20example%20of%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrist.org%2Fbusiness-technology%2Fnone-of-the-worlds-top-industries-would-be-profitable-if-they-paid-for-the-natural-capital-they-use%2F%5C%22%3Ereal%20costs%20are%20absorbed%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20those%20on%20the%20peripheries%2C%20while%20benefits%20accrue%20in%20the%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPetroleum%E2%80%99s%20higher%20energy%20density%20shrank%20the%20space%20needed%20to%20carry%20fuel%20and%20expanded%20cargo%20space.%20It%20made%20possible%20the%20vast%20modern%20fleets%20of%20enormous%20shipping%20vessels%2C%20each%20carrying%20multiple%20trainloads%20of%20goods%20halfway%20around%20the%20world%20in%20a%20just%20a%20few%20weeks.%20Petroleum%20made%20it%20possible%20to%20build%20and%20sell%20billions%20of%20scooters%20and%20cars%20and%20trucks%20that%20could%20ferry%20people%20and%20goods%20to%20any%20remote%20little%20town%20or%20village%20left%20behind%20by%20rail%20networks.%20Petroleum%20paved%20the%20roads%20to%20reach%20there%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20food%20systems%20also%20became%20intimately%20tied%20to%20the%20abundance%20of%20cheap%20oil%2C%20from%20making%20artificial%20pesticides%2C%20and%20herbicides%E2%80%94upon%20which%20industrial%20agriculture%20depends%E2%80%94to%20the%20long-distance%20transport%20chains%20that%20get%20farm%20produce%20to%20consumers.%20The%20modern%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.postcarbon.org%2Fpublications%2Ffood-and-farming-transition%2F%5C%22%3Eindustrial%20food%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20requires%2C%20on%20average%2C%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Ffigure%2FEnergy-expended-in-producing-and-delivering-one-food-calorie-Approximately-73-calories_fig1_303895662%5C%22%3Eseven%20calories%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20energy%20expenditure%20for%20each%20calorie%20that%20it%20delivers%20to%20our%20plates.%20Petroleum%20made%20modern%20mining%20operations%20possible%20too%2C%20multiplying%20the%20rate%20of%20extraction%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visualcapitalist.com%2Fall-the-worlds-metals-and-minerals-in-one-visualization%2F%5C%22%3Eiron%2C%20copper%2C%20sand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20everything%20else%E2%80%94including%20more%20coal%20and%20petroleum.%20Petroleum%20made%20it%20possible%20to%20fly%20passenger%20(or%20war)%20planes%2C%20connecting%20(or%20killing)%20people%20around%20the%20world%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20oil-based%20economy%20allows%20labor%2C%20capital%2C%20raw%20materials%2C%20and%20goods%20to%20move%20more%20rapidly%20along%20much%20the%20same%20pathways%20that%20were%20established%20during%20the%20centuries%20of%20European%20colonialism%3A%20materials%20and%20labor%20extracted%20from%20the%20Global%20South%20accumulate%20their%20benefits%20in%20the%20Global%20North%20faster%20than%20ever.%20Those%20pathways%20are%20kept%20open%20by%20oil-guzzling%2C%20industrialised%20militaries.%20Oil%2C%20itself%2C%20is%20also%20the%20source%20of%20huge%20quantities%20of%20cheap%20raw%20materials%20that%20further%20bolster%20industrialism%20by%20providing%20wholly%20novel%20materials%2C%20now%20essential%20to%20our%20lives%3A%20plastics%2C%20coatings%2C%20lubricants%2C%20solvents%2C%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20dyes%2C%20textiles%2C%20and%20more.%20And%20it%20does%20this%20at%20a%20cost%20unmatchable%20by%20any%20other%20material%20or%20process%20available%20on%20Earth.%20It%20is%20the%20lifeblood%20of%20the%20industrial%20economy.%20And%20the%20control%20of%20its%20production%2C%20distribution%2C%20and%20acquisition%20is%20a%20principle%20driver%20of%20modern%20geopolitics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10113314%2FNHQ202211160200large.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10113314%2FNHQ202211160200large.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10113314%2FNHQ202211160200large-300x250.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10113314%2FNHQ202211160200large-1024x852.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700961%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22998%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENASA%E2%80%99s%20Space%20Launch%20System%20rocket%20carrying%20the%20Orion%20spacecraft%20launches%20on%20the%20Artemis%20I%20flight%20test%2C%20November%2016%2C%202022.%20Photo%3A%20Bill%20Ingalls%2FNASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20elites%20in%20the%20states%20at%20the%20peripheries%20of%20emerging%20petro-capitalism%20saw%20sense%20in%20adopting%20it%20within%20their%20own%20realms%2C%20furthering%20their%20own%20wealth%20and%20geopolitical%20advantage.%20Meanwhile%2C%20many%20of%20those%20people%20already%20long%20dispossessed%20and%20marginalised%20by%20millennia%20of%20feudalism%20or%20colonialism%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20pathway%20to%20liberation%20or%20improved%20socioeconomic%20status%2C%20looking%20to%20the%20West%20as%20a%20model%20of%20the%20good%20life.%20But%20others%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20still%20lived%20relatively%20free%20of%20feudal%20or%20statist%20systems%E2%80%94those%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20Adivasis%20or%20Indigenous%20peoples%E2%80%94were%20drawn%20into%20the%20industrial%20economy%20when%20it%20encroached%20upon%20them%2C%20unwanted%2C%20as%20the%20forces%20of%20capitalism%20and%20colonialism%20(and%20later%2C%20neocolonialism%20and%20internal%20colonialism)%20increasingly%20dispossessed%20them%20of%20their%20traditional%20lands%2C%20resources%2C%20land-based%20lifeways%2C%20and%20freedom%20of%20movement%2C%20privileging%20instead%20industrial%20mining%2C%20logging%2C%20damming%2C%20or%20other%20extractivism%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20outsiders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDecentralised%20Indian%20farming%20systems%20once%20provided%20more%20diversified%20diets%20based%20around%20a%20variety%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournalofethnicfoods.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs42779-019-0011-9%5C%22%3Emillets%2C%20pulses%2C%20and%20rices%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20rural%20hunger%20still%20climbed%20as%20the%20population%20grew%2C%20soils%20were%20destroyed%20by%20more%20intensive%20cultivation%2C%20and%20cash%20crops%20were%20mandated%2C%20especially%20during%20European%20colonisation.%20Finally%20the%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20embarked%20in%201964%2C%20increased%20crop%20yields%20for%20three%20decades%2C%20making%20India%20self-sufficient%20in%20food%20production%20by%20the%201990s.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7611098%2F%5C%22%3Eyields%20per%20acre%20stopped%20rising%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20that%2C%20while%20the%20population%20and%20soil%20destruction%20did%20not%2C%20necessitating%20further%20farmland%20expansion%20and%20intensification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20dynamics%20continue%20today.%20Whether%20by%20drawing%20people%20into%20its%20programme%20voluntarily%20or%20enmeshing%20them%20without%20fair%20possibility%20for%20them%20to%20opt%20out%2C%20the%20goal%20of%20linking%20everybody%20into%20this%20hegemonic%20system%20of%20high%20consumption%20and%20waste%20is%20what%20we%20now%20call%20%E2%80%98development.%E2%80%99%20It%20has%20reduced%20the%20number%20of%20people%20living%20more%20nomadic%20or%20subsistence-agrarian%20lives%2C%20while%20increasing%20the%20numbers%20of%20potential%20workers%20and%20consumers%2C%20expanding%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20market.%20Promising%20such%20a%20goal%20is%20a%20universal%20good%2C%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%20became%20a%20lauded%20program%20of%20governments%20everywhere%20and%20an%20altruistic%20vision%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20and%20uncountable%20NGOs%2C%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20%E2%80%98lifting%20people%20out%20of%20poverty%2C%E2%80%99%20though%20it%20frequently%20has%20the%20opposite%20effect.%20According%20to%20environmentalist%20Ashish%20Kothari%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.planetcritical.com%2Fp%2Fan-alternative-india-ashish-kothari%23details%5C%22%3E60%20million%20Indians%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20lost%20their%20lands%20in%20the%20name%20of%20%E2%80%98development.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20is%20touted%20as%20one%20of%20its%20great%20successes.%20This%20program%20restored%20food%20access%20to%20villagers%E2%80%94who%E2%80%99d%20been%20brought%20to%20the%20point%20of%20starvation%20due%20to%20disastrously%20extractivist%20colonial%20policies%20coupled%20with%20rising%20populations%E2%80%94by%20applying%20artificial%20fertilisers%20and%20other%20petrochemicals%20to%20their%20fields.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20also%20destroyed%20their%20soils%20and%20locked%20some%20farmers%20into%20spiralling%20debt.%20And%20while%20the%20general%20expansion%20of%20energy%20consumption%20and%20rising%20GDP%20are%20considered%20%E2%80%98development%2C%E2%80%99%20these%20too%20have%20ultimately%20been%20built%20upon%20a%20limited%20trove%20of%20combustible%20fossils%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fto-the-pm-from-kaziranga-an-open-letter-decrying-displacement-human-rights-violations%5C%22%3Econtinuing%20dispossession%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20marginalised%20groups%2C%20and%20other%20modes%20of%20environmental%20destruction.%20Yet%20choruses%20glorifying%20new%20feats%20of%20wealth%20and%20power%20continuously%20drown%20out%20the%20voices%20of%20the%20dispossessed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112518%2FGlobal-CO2-IEA-2023.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22606%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112518%2FGlobal-CO2-IEA-2023.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112518%2FGlobal-CO2-IEA-2023-300x132.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112518%2FGlobal-CO2-IEA-2023-1024x450.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700958%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22266%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGlobal%20carbon-dioxide%20emissions%20have%20risen%20dramatically%20over%20the%20past%20several%20decades%2C%20slowed%20only%20periodically%20by%20global%20crises%20like%20economic%20recession%2C%20war%2C%20and%20pandemic.%20Chart%3A%20IEA%20report%2C%20%E2%80%9CCO2%20Emissions%20in%202022%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20other%20energy%20source%20we%20know%20of%20can%20make%20so%20cheap%20and%20easy%20what%20petroleum%20has%20made%20so%20cheap%20and%20easy.%20It%20is%20the%20modern%20human%20superpower.%20Unlike%20the%20first%20one%E2%80%94that%20original%20fire%20that%20made%20us%20human%2C%20once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbecoming-human-forged-by-fire%5C%22%3Eunderstood%20as%20a%20gift%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20gods%20entailing%20a%20pact%2C%20an%20entanglement%20with%20questions%20of%20morality%20and%20responsibility%E2%80%94we%20have%20conflated%20this%20newer%20power%20with%20ourselves%2C%20swallowed%20it%20within%20our%20hubris.%20Yet%20it%20bears%20reflecting%20that%20it%20too%20comes%20freighted%20with%20costs%20and%20moral%20entanglements.%20That%20the%20global%20boom%20in%20wealth%20of%20the%20last%20seventy%20years%20is%20not%20primarily%20due%20to%20smarter%20politics%20or%20technologies%20or%20superior%20knowledge%20systems%20or%20any%20of%20the%20self-congratulatory%20stories%20we%20like%20to%20tell%20ourselves.%20None%20of%20that%20would%20go%20anywhere%20without%20oil.%20And%E2%80%94let%E2%80%99s%20not%20fool%20ourselves%E2%80%94without%20oil%2C%20it%20will%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20376px)%2085vw%2C%20376px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22376%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%20874w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%20746w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696598%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22516%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20combustible%20fossils%E2%80%94petroleum%2C%20coal%2C%20and%20gas%E2%80%94are%20gifts%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fa-planetary-perspective%5C%22%3Ethe%20late%20Paleozoic%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20trees%20grew%20and%20fell%20in%20heaps%2C%20when%20great%20blooms%20of%20plankton%20and%20algae%20sank%20under%20the%20silt%20of%20the%20seas.%20All%20their%20remains%2C%20collected%20together%20in%20mountainous%20quantities%20and%20pressed%20down%20over%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20years%2C%20encapsulate%20the%20stored%20energy%20of%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20years%20of%20sunlight%20that%20had%20fallen%20to%20Earth%20before%20the%20reign%20of%20the%20dinosaurs.%20That%20chemical%20potential%20had%20lain%20dormant%20in%20the%20belly%20of%20the%20Earth%2C%20taken%20out%20of%20circulation%20from%20the%20living%20systems%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20humans%20have%20resurrected%20that%20chemistry%20in%20a%20sudden%20burst.%20Its%20eruption%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20over%20the%20past%20three%20hundred%20years%E2%80%94a%20veritable%20explosion%20on%20geological%20timescales%E2%80%94cannot%20occur%20without%20also%20violently%20altering%20the%20biogeochemistry%20of%20our%20planet.%20This%20is%20the%20climate%20and%20ecological%20crisis%20we%20now%20live%20within.%20By%20several%20measures%2C%20the%20havoc%20it%E2%80%99s%20wrought%20leaves%20us%20at%20best%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fsep%2F13%2Fearth-well-outside-safe-operating-space-for-humanity-scientists-find%3FCMP%3DShare_iOSApp_Other%5C%22%3Eteetering%20on%20the%20brink%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20exceeding%20the%20ecological%20safety%20zone%20for%20humankind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20this%20glut%20of%20cheap%2C%20fossilised%20energy%20is%20limited%2C%20a%20one-time%20deal%20that%20can%20never%20be%20replicated%20in%20any%20human%20timeframe.%20Today%E2%80%99s%20oil%20will%20reach%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.e-education.psu.edu%2Femsc470%2Fnode%2F557%5C%22%3Eits%20own%20limit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20it%20simply%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2019%2F07%2F190711114846.htm%5C%22%3Etakes%20more%20energy%20to%20gather%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20fast%20enough%20to%20expand%20the%20economy%20than%20what%20it%20returns.%20Meanwhile%2C%20like%20an%20addict%2C%20the%20industrial%20economic%20beast%20is%20already%20desperately%20slurping%20up%20the%20lowest-quality%20dregs%20from%20so-called%20%3Cem%3Etight%20oil%3C%2Fem%3E%20sources%20(as%20opposed%20to%20%3Cem%3Econventional%20oil%3C%2Fem%3E%20sources).%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2666049022000524%5C%22%3Edays%20of%20oil%20abundance%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjpt.spe.org%2Fplummeting-energy-return-on-investment-of-oil-and-the-impact-on-global-energy-landscape%5C%22%3Enumbered%20in%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F343768755_The_Resource-Limited_Plateau_in_Global_Conventional_Oil_Production_Analysis_and_Consequences%5C%22%3Enot%20decades%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Without%20cheap%20oil%20to%20help%20build%20and%20power%20mining%20operations%2C%20access%20to%20coal%20and%20gas%20would%20also%20be%20diminished%2C%20the%20necessary%20rate%20and%20scale%20rendered%20economically%E2%80%94if%20not%20also%20logistically%E2%80%94unfeasible%20using%20other%20power%20sources.%20Continuing%20to%20increase%20our%20dependency%20on%20these%20fossils%20in%20any%20way%20makes%20literally%20no%20Earthly%20sense.%20We%20must%20instead%20imagine%20a%20system%20that%20moves%20away%20from%20burning%20fossils%2C%20altogether%2C%20rap%C2%A0idly%20and%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20586px)%2085vw%2C%20586px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22586%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023-300x211.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023-1024x721.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700959%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22413%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20rate%20at%20which%20we%20must%20phase%20out%20fossil%20fuel%20sources%20and%20adjust%20land-use%20practices%20for%20a%2067%25%20chance%20of%20limiting%20global%20warming%20thresholds%20of%201.5%C2%BAC%20(green)%2C%201.7%C2%BAC%20(blue)%2C%20or%202.0%C2%BAC%20red.%20Chart%3A%20Friedlingstein%20et%20al%202023%20(https%3A%2F%2Fessd.copernicus.org%2Farticles%2F15%2F5301%2F2023%2Fessd-15-5301-2023.html)%3B%20Global%20Carbon%20Project%202023%20(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalcarbonproject.org%2Fcarbonbudget%2F)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20already%20built%20a%20world%20that%E2%80%99s%20now%20well%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3Estate%20of%20ecological%20overshoot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20locked%20into%20capitalism%E2%80%99s%20requirement%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fof-mice-and-men-energy-and-cancer%5C%22%3Egrowth%20in%20consumption%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20to%20keep%20the%20present%20system%20afloat%3A%20to%20keep%20the%20goods%20flowing%2C%20the%20steel%20and%20concrete%20rising%2C%20the%20institutions%20flush%20with%20resources%20for%20research%20and%20education%20and%20policymaking%2C%20the%20factories%20supplied%20with%20raw%20materials%20and%20industrial%20chemicals%E2%80%94many%20of%20which%20are%20directly%20sourced%20from%20petroleum.%20As%20a%20living%20system%20set%20upon%20a%20trajectory%20of%20unabated%20growth%2C%20our%20economy%20requires%20the%20massive%20overconsumption%20of%20both%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20even%20as%20it%20destroys%20the%20living%20systems%20of%20the%20world%20upon%20which%20it%20depends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20crux%20of%20our%20predicament%3A%20Consumption%2C%20growth%2C%20socioeconomic%20wellbeing%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20inequalities%2C%20exploitation%2C%20pollution%2C%20species%20genocide%2C%20ecosystem%20annihilation%2C%20and%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20form%20a%20nexus%20of%20interdependencies%20that%20feed%20and%20perpetuate%20one%20another%20as%20the%20basis%20of%20modern%20global%20civilisation.%20This%20system%20is%20both%20unsustainable%20over%20time%20as%20well%20as%20immediately%20destructive%20for%20great%20multitudes%2C%20both%20human%20and%20non-human%2C%20even%20while%20we%20have%20made%20it%20foundational%20to%20the%20dreams%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20billions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20deployed%20thirsty%2C%20high-yielding%20strains%20of%20wheat%20and%20rice%20that%20grew%20well%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20artificial%20fertilisers%2C%20herbicides%2C%20and%20pesticides.%20As%20with%20any%20%E2%80%98progress%20trap%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20short-term%20benefits%20gained%20cannot%20overcome%20the%20long-term%20costs%20incurred%2C%20including%20soil%20destruction%3B%20groundwater%20depletion%3B%20chemical%20pollution%20of%20land%2C%20water%2C%20and%20people%3B%20loss%20of%20insects%20and%20other%20biodiversity%3B%20narrowing%20of%20the%20Indian%20diet%3B%20and%20extinction%20of%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fgrains-of-life-how-chotanagpurs-adivasis-are-reviving-native-varieties-of-rice%5C%22%3Eone%20lakh%20varieties%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20indigenous%20seeds%2C%20shrinking%20the%20available%20gene%20pool%20for%20food%20grains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20combustible%20fossil%20revolution%E2%80%94with%20a%20special%20emphasis%20on%20oil%E2%80%94absolutely%20underwrites%20the%20modern%20way%20of%20life.%20It%20has%20provided%20continuous%20growth%20in%20energy%20use%2C%20which%20%3Cem%3Ecannot%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20replicated%20by%20less%20concentrated%2C%20more%20unreliable%2C%20and%20seasonally%20or%20diurnally%20limited%20renewable%20sources.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20already%20know%20this.%20Why%20else%20would%20we%20Indians%20have%20argued%20for%20entitlements%20to%20burn%20more%20fossils%2C%20justified%20only%20by%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20rise%20to%20economic%20dominance%20by%20having%20done%20it%20first%3F%20If%20we%20believed%20%E2%80%98renewables%E2%80%99%20were%20a%20complete%20answer%2C%20we%20would%20gladly%20leapfrog%20the%20need%20for%20combustible%20fossils%20and%20build%20the%20great%20and%20%E2%80%98clean%E2%80%99%20Indian%20industrial%20economy.%20But%20despite%20all%20the%20%E2%80%98hope%E2%80%99%20elites%20declaim%20around%20%E2%80%98greening%E2%80%99%20our%20energy%20systems%2C%20we%20intuitively%20understand%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20way%20to%20have%20the%20%E2%80%98developed%2C%E2%80%99%20capitalist-consumerist%20economy%20without%20breaking%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20all%20the%20%E2%80%98renewable%E2%80%99%20energy%E2%80%94which%20is%20delivered%20to%20us%20only%20through%20installations%20that%20are%20%3Cem%3Enot%20at%20all%20renewable%3C%2Fem%3E%20but%20%3Cem%3Emust%20be%20built%20and%20re-built%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20every%20few%20decades%E2%80%94thus%20far%20deployed%20haven%E2%80%99t%20begun%20to%20reduce%20our%20fossil%20fuel%20consumption.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fourworldindata.org%2Fgrapher%2Felectricity-prod-source-stacked%5C%22%3Eonly%20added%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20our%20overall%20energy%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20581px)%2085vw%2C%20581px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22581%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution-300x212.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution-1024x723.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700960%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22410%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERenewable%20energy%20sources%20haven%E2%80%99t%20reduced%20our%20demand%20for%20combustible%20fossils.%20They%20have%20only%20allowed%20us%20to%20increase%20our%20overall%20energy%20consumption.%20Chart%3A%20Our%20World%20in%20Data%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20exposes%20the%20terrible%20reality%20that%20we%20%3Cem%3Ecannot%3C%2Fem%3E%20reduce%20our%20fossil%20fuel%20consumption%E2%80%94and%20associated%20carbon%20emissions%E2%80%94until%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jasonhickel.org%2Fblog%2F2023%2F11%2F24%2Fhow-popular-are-post-growth-and-post-capitalist-ideas%5C%22%3Estop%20growing%20the%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ending%20fossil-fuelled%20emissions%20means%20transitioning%20to%20a%20reduced%20energy-and-materials%20consumption%20economy.%20This%20requires%20simultaneously%20innovating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fd41586-022-04412-x%5C%22%3Ealternate%20modes%20of%20social%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20provisioning%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20allows%20other%20living%20systems%20also%20to%20flourish.%20It%20is%20the%20only%20viable%20path%20forward.%20This%20means%20prioritizing%20the%20uses%20of%20a%20limited%20energy%20budget%20in%20a%20way%20that%20equitably%20benefits%20the%20greatest%20number%20of%20people.%20And%20this%20implies%20austerity%20for%20the%20rich%E2%80%94indeed%2C%20a%20phase-out%20of%20wealth%20inequality%20and%20the%20mechanisms%20that%20create%20and%20maintain%20it.%20Taken%20together%2C%20this%20becomes%20an%20absolutely%20fundamental%20re-envisioning%20and%20restructuring%20of%20global%20society%20and%20the%20principles%20by%20which%20it%20functions%E2%80%94our%20social%20structures%2C%20value%20systems%2C%20identities%2C%20mythologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocieties%20do%20change%2C%20of%20course.%20They%20never%20stop%20changing%2C%20whether%20by%20consent%20or%20force%20of%20circumstance.%20For%20better%20or%20for%20worse.%20And%20that%20social%20change%20always%20entails%20an%20evolution%20in%20the%20stories%20we%20tell%20ourselves%2C%20for%20it%20is%20our%20stories%20that%20build%20the%20world%20we%20inhabit%E2%80%94as%20much%20as%20they%20can%20also%20blind%20us%20to%20other%20aspects%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20next%20essay%20will%20touch%20upon%20this%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Only%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710050720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112000%2FIMG_2968.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Continuing%20to%20increase%20our%20dependency%20on%20these%20fossils%20in%20any%20way%20makes%20literally%20no%20Earthly%20sense.%20We%20must%20instead%20imagine%20a%20system%20that%20moves%20away%20from%20burning%20fossils%2C%20altogether%2C%20rap%C2%A0idly%20and%20completely.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'To%20Kill%20a%20Tiger'%20Chronicles%20a%20Father's%20Pursuit%20of%20Justice%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Strength%20of%20Women%20Around%20Him%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10111355%2FTo-Kill-a-Tiger-02.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20glitzy%20Oscars%20scene%2C%20where%20gowns%20and%20tuxedos%20steal%20the%20show%2C%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20best%20documentary%20contenders%2C%20including%20Nisha%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20A%20Tiger%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20explore%20family%2C%20social%20justice%2C%20book%20banning%2C%20war%20and%20politics.%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20two-hour%20feature%20stands%20out%2C%20chronicling%20a%20father%E2%80%99s%20unwavering%20pursuit%20of%20justice%20for%20his%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20sat%20down%20to%20write%20a%20review%20of%20this%20heart-rattlingly%20urgent%20documentary%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fjharkhand-13-year-old-girl-killed-for-resisting-rape-attempt-in-godda%5C%22%3Enews%20%3C%2Fa%3Etrickled%20down%20about%20yet%20another%20killing%20of%2013-year-old%20girl.%20She%20was%20allegedly%20killed%20in%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20Godda%20district%20after%20she%20resisted%20an%20attempt%20of%20rape%20by%20two%20men%20aged%2021%20who%20have%20confessed%20to%20committing%20the%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20weighs%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20vast%20media%20universe%2C%20stories%20of%20sexual%20assault%20often%20fade%20away%2C%20lost%20in%20overloaded%20legal%20processes%20or%20swallowed%20by%20toxic%20masculinity.%20Yet%2C%20%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20A%20Tiger%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20cinematic%20documentary%2C%20purposefully%20unveils%20real-life%20stories%2C%20urging%20broader%20attention%20to%20the%20rampant%20epidemic%20of%20misogynistic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETending%20to%20the%20rice%20fields%2C%20Ranjit%20%E2%80%93%20the%20doting%20father%20to%20his%20daughter%2C%20the%20victim%20of%20a%20sexual%20assault%20in%202017%20%E2%80%93%20shares%20a%20poignant%20revelation%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20film.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20once%20told%2C%20%E2%80%98You%20can%E2%80%99t%20kill%20a%20tiger%20by%20yourself%2C'%E2%80%9D%20recounts%20Ranjit%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99ll%20show%20you%20how%20to%20kill%20a%20tiger%20all%20by%20yourself.%E2%80%99%20And%20so%2C%20I%20did.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20sets%20up%20the%20narrative%20arc%20of%20the%20tale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Emotional%20journey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForged%20over%20the%20course%20of%20eight%20years%2C%20the%20documentary%2C%20winner%20of%20more%20than%2020%20awards%20at%20festivals%20around%20the%20world%2C%20highlights%20the%20pervasive%20and%20deeply%20rooted%20nature%20of%20male%20violence%20against%20females%20ingrained%20in%20the%20fabric%20of%20our%20society.%20How%20does%20one%20tell%20such%20a%20story%3F%20Caught%20in%20the%20spotlight%2C%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20stance%20captivates%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Srijan%20Foundation%2C%20an%20NGO%20dedicated%20to%20sensitising%20men%20and%20boys%20about%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20They%20see%20in%20Ranjit%20a%20symbol%20for%20their%20cause%2C%20a%20beacon%20of%20inspiration%20for%20other%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20Delhi-born%20Canadian%20director%20Nisha%20Pahuja%20says%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20a%20Tiger%20%3C%2Fem%3Eactually%20started%20off%20as%20an%20entirely%20different%20film.%20That%20film%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESend%C2%A0Us%20Your%20Brother%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20a%20more%20pointed%20and%20direct%20exploration%20of%20Indian%20masculinity.%20The%20focus%20of%20the%20original%20work%20was%20Mahendra%20Kumar%2C%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20activist%20who%20has%20a%20key%2C%20albeit%20minor%2C%20role%20in%20the%20film.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20as%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20story%20emerged%20from%20a%20programme%20led%20by%20Mahendra%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20the%20director%20recognised%20its%20potential%20as%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20backbone%2C%20with%20his%20work%20and%20personal%20life%20adding%20a%20broader%20context%20to%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20a%20Tiger%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Echarts%20the%20emotional%20journey%20of%20an%20ordinary%20man%20thrown%20into%20extraordinary%20circumstances%20%E2%80%93%20a%20father%20whose%20love%20for%20his%20daughter%20forces%20a%20social%20reckoning%20that%20will%20reverberate%20for%20years%20to%20come.%20The%20allure%20of%20this%20approach%20stemmed%20from%20its%20simplicity.%20It%20offers%20a%20continuity%20to%20a%20rich%20body%20of%20works%20that%20Pahuja%20has%20undertaken%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20like%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20short%20film%20for%20%3Cem%3EGlobal%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20investigative%20news%20and%20current%20affairs%20programme%2016%C3%979%20%E2%80%98Indian%20Bus%20Outrage%E2%80%99%2C%20investigating%20flaws%20in%20the%20justice%20system%20in%20India%20following%20the%20brutal%202012%20gang%20rape%20and%20murder%20of%20a%20young%20woman%20on%20a%20bus%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20It%20was%20a%20recipient%20of%20an%20Amnesty%20International%20media%20award%20for%20Canadian%20journalism%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FmC6-igJ_WWM%3Fsi%3D6mZeRndBdacBfDeV%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPahuja%20approached%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20complex%20situation%20with%20a%20keen%20understanding%20of%20its%20layered%20sensitivity.%20With%20prior%20experience%20directing%20films%20in%20India%2C%20notably%20%3Cem%3EThe%20World%20Before%20Her%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2012)%20that%20juxtaposed%20the%20competition%20among%20women%20aspiring%20to%20be%20Miss%20India%20with%20Hindu%20nationalists%20defending%20their%20beliefs%20(awarded%20Best%20Canadian%20Feature%20at%20the%20Hot%20Docs%20Canadian%20International%20Documentary%20Festival)%2C%20she%20was%20mindful%20not%20to%20take%20sides%20in%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20fabric%2C%20intimate%20scenes%20from%20village%20gatherings%20reveal%20a%20spectrum%20of%20perspectives%2C%20featuring%20voices%20even%20from%20the%20fathers%20of%20the%20accused.%20Yet%2C%20as%20the%20legal%20proceedings%20persist%2C%20a%20faction%20of%20villagers%20resorts%20to%20coercive%20tactics%20against%20Ranjit%20%E2%80%93%20employing%20emotional%20manipulation%2C%20proffering%20bribes%20and%20escalating%20to%20threats%20of%20arson%20and%20murder.%20This%20mounting%20tension%20culminates%20in%20an%20increasing%20animosity%20directed%20at%20the%20film%20crew%20earnestly%20documenting%20these%20unfolding%20and%20unsettling%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20narrative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPahuja%E2%80%99s%20husband%2C%20Mrinal%20Desai%2C%20wields%20the%20camera%20like%20a%20poet%E2%80%99s%20pen.%20He%20deftly%20captures%20the%20village%E2%80%99s%20serenity%2C%20meandering%20through%20its%20tranquil%20spaces%20and%20deciphering%20the%20unspoken%20dialect%20of%20gazes%20%E2%80%93%20all%20the%20while%20encapsulating%20the%20hidden%20subterranean%20explosiveness%20simmering%20beneath%20the%20narrative%E2%80%99s%20surface.%20As%20if%20drawing%20inspiration%20from%20the%20locale%2C%20a%20mining%20town%20famed%20for%20its%20rich%20mineral%20veins%2C%20the%20cinematographer%20moulds%20haptic%20images%2C%20extracting%20their%20nuanced%20meanings%20and%20tensions.%20The%20cinematic%20shots%20in%20the%20labyrinth%20of%20courts%20in%20Ranchi%20reminds%20one%20of%20his%20early%20work%20in%20Chaitanya%20Tamhane%E2%80%99s%20Marathi-language%20courtroom%20drama%2C%20%3Cem%3ECourt%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cinematic%20narrative%20commences%20with%20Ranjit%20articulating%20the%20profound%20experience%20of%20welcoming%20his%20daughter%2C%20Kiran%2C%20into%20the%20world.%20He%20cloaks%20her%20in%20the%20entirety%20of%20his%20affection%2C%20challenging%20the%20notion%20that%20love%20transcends%20the%20confines%20of%20material%20reality.%20With%20her%20penchant%20for%20narrative-driven%20films%2C%20Pahuja%20crafts%20intricately%20woven%20worlds%20that%20captivate%20with%20their%20visual%20splendour%20%E2%80%93%20a%20close-up%20of%20Kiran%20braiding%20her%20hair%20with%20colourful%20ribbons%20%E2%80%93%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Spanish%20filmmaker%20Isabel%20Coixet.%20More%20so%2C%20it%20is%20particularly%20apparent%20in%20her%20silent%20portrayal%20of%20Kiran%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20highlighting%20her%20steadfast%20silent%20presence%20and%20the%20nuanced%20dynamics%20of%20her%20relationship%20with%20her%20husband%20Ranjit.%20The%20deliberate%20manner%20in%20which%20she%20guides%20and%20supports%20him%20during%20his%20moments%20of%20vulnerability%20underscores%20her%20inherent%20strength.%C2%A0%20Wrestling%20with%20the%20profound%20intricacies%20of%20human%20existence%20remains%20a%20constant%20in%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20exploration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20National%20Film%20Board%20of%20Canada-funded%20documentary%2C%20her%20storytelling%2C%20delicately%20rendered%2C%20possesses%20a%20distinctly%20feminine%20and%20sensual%20allure.%20That%20made%20me%20think%20of%20Jane%20Campion%2C%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20contemporary%20filmmakers%2C%20and%20her%20classic%20short%20%E2%80%93%20a%20tightly%20controlled%20nine-minute%20drama%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EPeel%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1982)%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Piano%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1993)%20and%20more%20recent%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Power%20of%20the%20Dog%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021).%20Though%20a%20tale%20of%20the%20father%E2%80%99s%20pursuit%2C%20this%20film%20is%20predominantly%20concerned%20with%20female%20characters%20struggling%20to%20be%20heard%2C%20recognised%20and%20understood.%20The%20intricacies%20of%20other%20figures%20in%20the%20tale%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20the%20Ward%20Member%2C%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20wife%20Jaganti%2C%20and%2C%20most%20notably%2C%20his%20daughter%20Kiran%20%E2%80%93%20unfold%20in%20delicate%20layers.%20While%20Kiran%20undeniably%20survives%20a%20brutal%20crime%2C%20her%20character%20transcends%20simplistic%20victimhood%2C%20revealing%20nuanced%20facets%20that%20enrich%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEthics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20ethics%20govern%20her%20art.%20%E2%80%9CDiscussing%20morality%20without%20considering%20the%20ethics%20of%20filming%20a%20survivor%2C%20especially%20a%20child%2C%20would%20be%20a%20lapse%20on%20my%20part.%20Initially%20hiding%20Kiran%E2%80%99s%20identity%20complied%20with%20Indian%20law%20and%20felt%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20reflects.%20However%2C%20grappling%20with%20the%20prevailing%20cultural%20stigma%2C%20she%20questions%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20not%20showing%20her%2C%20am%20I%20perpetuating%20the%20bias%20I%20critique%3F%20Yet%2C%20imposing%20my%20perspective%20on%20a%20vulnerable%20child%20feels%20unjust.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20emerging%20to%20be%20a%20thorny%20issue.%20Anna%20M.M.%20Vetticad%2C%20author%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Adventures%20of%20an%20Intrepid%20Film%20Critic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20points%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.himalmag.com%2Fculture%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-oscars-india-rape-pocso%5C%22%3Eethical%20and%20legal%20violations%3C%2Fa%3E%20inherent%20in%20the%20making%20of%20the%20film.%20The%20issue%20of%20filming%20a%20minor%20rape%20victim%20makes%20it%20vulnerable%20for%20the%20filmmaker%2C%20given%20the%20stringent%20guidelines%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20(POCSO)%20Act%202012.%20The%20victim%E2%80%99s%20parent%E2%80%99s%20permission%20does%20not%20suffice%2C%20one%20has%20to%20get%20a%20directive%20from%20a%20special%20court%20if%20it%20deems%20in%20its%20view%20that%20such%20disclosure%20aligns%20with%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20child%20involved.%20Meanwhile%20another%20Canadian%20filmmaker%2C%20Leena%20Manimekalai%2C%20has%20patently%20dismissed%20the%20film%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLeenaManimekali%2Fstatus%2F1746228215671079068%5C%22%3Ea%20classic%20example%20of%20a%20settler%20colonist%20gaze%20on%20an%20indigenous%20child%20survivor%20of%20gang%20rape%20in%20a%20developing%20country%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%2C%20Kiran%20existed%20as%20both%20a%20child%20and%20a%20survivor.%20Today%20in%20her%2020th%20year%2C%20Kiran%20is%20so%20much%20more.%20She%20stands%20tall%20and%20looks%20out%20to%20a%20brighter%20future%20and%20wonders%20about%20falling%20in%20love%20and%20what%20she%20will%20tell%20her%20beloved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20my%20hope%20that%20collectively%20we%20empower%20her%20and%20support%20her%20healing%20as%20part%20of%20this%20film%E2%80%99s%20journey%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20a%20journey%20with%20impact%20at%20its%20heart%2C%20and%20one%20that%E2%80%99s%20being%20planned%20carefully%20and%20strategically%20with%20lawyers%2C%20documentary%20impact%20strategists%2C%20therapists%20and%20an%20advisory%20council%20made%20up%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20and%20human%20rights%20organisations%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Pahuja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20list%20of%20executive%20producers%20that%20are%20attached%20to%20this%20film%20including%20Dev%20Patel%2C%20Mindy%20Kailing%2C%20poet%20Rupi%20Kaur%2C%20Dr%20Atul%20Gawande%20and%20Priyanka%20Chopra%20Jonas%2C%20to%20ensure%20this%20story%20does%20what%20it%20can%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20the%20distressing%20news%20of%20yet%20another%20assault%20on%20a%2013-year%20old%20girl%20in%20the%20same%20region%20filtering%20through%2C%20the%20sickening%20irony%20piles%20up%2C%20each%20layer%20adding%20a%20punch%20to%20the%20gut%20within%20the%20narrative%20of%20this%20documentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENarendra%20Pachkh%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%A9%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Ed%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%A9%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20critic%20and%20writer%20who%C2%A0splits%20his%20time%20between%20Toronto%2C%20London%20and%20Geneva.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710049542000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10111355%2FTo-Kill-a-Tiger-02.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-nisha-pahuja%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nisha%20Pahuja's%20Oscar-nominated%20cinematic%20documentary%20purposefully%20unveils%20real-life%20stories%2C%20urging%20broader%20attention%20to%20the%20rampant%20epidemic%20of%20misogynistic%20violence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-nisha-pahuja%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Designer%20Donatella%20Versace%20rescued%20from%20lift%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710047615000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F0705%2Fproduction%2F_132879710_gettyimages-2065217786.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68526494%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20took%20several%20people%20to%20hold%20the%20elevator%20doors%20open%20to%20allow%20the%20fashion%20designer%20a%20tight%20escape.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A60%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68526494%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68526494.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68526494.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chandigarh%3A%20BJP%20Loses%20Majority%20in%20Municipal%20Corp%20as%202%20AAP%20Turncoats%20Return%20to%20INDIA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10103612%2FAAP-MC.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20drama%20in%20the%20Chandigarh%20Municipal%20Corporation%20(MC)%20is%20far%20from%20over.%20In%20the%20latest%20move%2C%20two%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20councillors%20who%20had%20defected%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20last%20month%20returned%20to%20the%20party%20fold%20on%20Saturday%20(March%209).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20changed%20the%20numbers%20game%20in%2035-member%20Chandigarh%20MC%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20AAP-Congress%20alliance%2C%20which%20had%20earlier%20been%20left%20a%20disadvantage%20despite%20their%20mayor%20being%20reinstated%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKuldeep%20Kumar%20was%20declared%20the%20validly%20elected%20Chandigarh%20mayor%20on%20February%2021%20in%20a%20historic%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%2C%20which%20reversed%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20rigged%20mayoral%20elections%20decided%20fraudulently%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20BJP%20candidate%20by%20presiding%20officer%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20now%20facing%20SC-monitored%20criminal%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20members%20of%20the%20AAP-Congress%20alliance%20were%20worried%20that%20the%20rival%20BJP%20could%20unseat%20their%20mayor%20any%20time%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20because%20defection%20by%20three%20AAP%20councillors%20had%20tilted%20the%20MC%20majority%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20saffron%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20poached%20these%20AAP%20councillors%20before%20the%20SC%20order%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20it%20case%20of%20a%20fresh%20mayoral%20election%2C%20it%20could%20come%20up%20the%20winner.%C2%A0But%20the%20apex%20court%20reinstated%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20candidate%2C%20catching%20the%20BJP%20by%20surprise%20and%20also%20leaving%20it%20humiliated%20since%20the%20guilty%20presiding%20officer%20was%20a%20BJP%20appointee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20did%20get%20some%20poll%20advantage%20from%20the%20AAP%20defectors%20as%20it%20won%20re-election%20on%20the%20post%20of%20senior%20deputy%20mayor%20and%20deputy%20mayor%20on%20March%204.%20But%20it%20is%20no%20longer%20in%20a%20commanding%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scale%20now%20favours%20the%20INDIA%20block%20as%20two%20AAP%20councillors%20%E2%80%93%20Poonam%20and%20Neha%20%E2%80%93%20took%20AAP%20membership%20again%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECouncillor%20Neha%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20shared%20by%20AAP%20with%20the%20media%20that%20while%20living%20together%2C%20discords%20occur.%20The%20same%20thing%20happened%20here%20between%20the%20party%20and%20her.%20But%20now%20she%20has%20decided%20to%20forget%20this%20and%20return%20home.%20Councillor%20Poonam%20said%20that%20now%20she%20has%20no%20problem%20and%20she%20is%20very%20happy%20to%20return%20to%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20they%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20fresh%20comments%20on%20Sunday%2C%20their%20return%20has%20nonetheless%20put%20the%20AAP-Congress%20alliance%20in%20a%20comfortable%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20latest%20numbers%2C%20AAP%20now%20has%2012%20councillors%20while%20the%20Congress%20has%20seven.%20Together%2C%20the%20two%20parties%20have%2019%20councillors%2C%20more%20than%20required%20number%20for%20a%20majority%20in%20the%2035-member%20Chandigarh%20Municipal%20Corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20councillors%20rejoined%20AAP%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20Punjab%20chief%20minister%20Bhagwant%20Mann%E2%80%99s%20OSD%20Rajbir%20Singh%20Ghumman%20and%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20Chandigarh%20co-incharge%20Sunny%20Singh%20Ahluwalia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20former%20Chandigarh%20incharge%20Prem%20Garg%20said%20that%20the%20party%20welcomed%20both%20the%20councillors%20after%20they%20realised%20their%20mistake%20and%20agreed%20to%20return%20to%20the%20party%20unconditionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CINDIA%20bloc%20will%20do%20everything%20to%20improve%20the%20lives%20of%20Chandigarh%E2%80%99s%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20third%20AAP%20councillor%20who%20jumped%20ship%2C%20Gurcharan%20Singh%20Kala%2C%20is%20still%20with%20the%20BJP.%20AAP%20sources%20said%20he%20is%20being%20pursued%20to%20return%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710047237000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10103612%2FAAP-MC.jpg%22%2C%22